# Mobile-Web Parity Contract

## The Rule

The mobile Verdict page (`mobile/app/verdict.tsx`) MUST mirror the web Verdict page
(`frontend/src/app/verdict/page.tsx`) section-for-section. When one changes, the other
MUST be updated in the same PR/commit.

## Canonical Section Order

Both platforms render sections in this order, defined by `VERDICT_SECTIONS` in
`@dealscope/shared` (`shared/src/types/verdict.ts`):

```
1. photo              — property image
2. investmentOverview — Target Buy (Profit Zone), Income Value (Break-Even), Market Price (Market Reality)
3. priceScaleBar      — gradient bar with dots for Target/Income/Market, Deal Gap + Price Gap brackets
4. marketAnchorNote   — listed vs off-market explanation
5. dataSources        — expandable accordion with IQ Estimate selector (web only for v1)
6. dealGapExplanation — "The DealGap" panel with %, tier pill, guidance, methodology
7. keyInsights        — numbered insight items with expand/collapse
8. actionButtons      — Change Terms (+ export buttons on web)
9. cta                — "Now Prove It" / "Show Me the Numbers"
10. trustStrip        — bottom credibility line
```

## Shared Verdict Response Type

Both platforms MUST import `IQVerdictResponse` from `@dealscope/shared` for the
`POST /api/v1/analysis/verdict` response. Do NOT define local verdict response types.

```typescript
// CORRECT
import type { IQVerdictResponse } from '@dealscope/shared';

// WRONG — local type will drift
interface VerdictAnalysis { ... }
interface BackendAnalysisResponse { ... }
```

## Forbidden Patterns on Verdict Page

```typescript
// NEVER show deal_score as a hero metric on Verdict
<ScoreGauge score={analysis.deal_score} />     // Verdict page — FORBIDDEN
<Text>{analysis.deal_score}</Text>             // Verdict page — FORBIDDEN

// deal_score IS allowed on Strategy and DealMaker pages
// as a compact summary metric

// NEVER show strategy grid or LTR investment metrics on Verdict
<StrategyGrid strategies={...} />              // FORBIDDEN on Verdict
<InvestmentMetrics capRate={...} />            // FORBIDDEN on Verdict
```

## When Modifying the Verdict Page

1. Check `VERDICT_SECTIONS` in `shared/src/types/verdict.ts`
2. Make the change on the platform you're editing (web or mobile)
3. Make the equivalent change on the other platform
4. If adding/removing/reordering sections, update `VERDICT_SECTIONS`

